description: This book collects reprinted rarities from National/DC Comics' 70 years of being and is chocked full of little known behind the scenes history lessons. This book is a must own for fans of DC that missed out on the ground floor of their rise to what we know and love today. Also features a forward by Paul Levits and a gleaming quote from Stan Lee on the back cover
name: The DC Vault

description: This book tells the tale of an aged Hans Von Hammer being interviewed by a curious reporter that has seen the horrors of a more modern war himself. Emotions run high as tales from both men's pasts are brought to surface revealing why they fought and more importantly, how they would cope?
name: Enemy Ace: War Idyll

A sudden rain of fish is the beginning of the newest adventure of Charles Fort, New York librarian, seeker of truth and self-proclaimed foremost authority on the unexplained. A rash of murders has the city in panicked and Governor Theodore Roosevelt demands answers. Can Fort and his unlikely companion provide these before they are arrested and hanged by the city's mistaken police force?

description:
Her name is Iris Allen and she is the fastest girl alive. After the U.S.A lost Kansas, parts of Nebraska, Iowa and Missouri the world worked hard to make the world a utopia. Iris spends her days delivering meals to the elderly as well as trying to get in touch with her father (Wally West) and make him see she is right to claim the Mantle "Kid Flash" Her brother, however Barry West pushed her over and eats the meals, he shows her what their father said. That the world is going to end in a day, Barry spends the day relaxing while Iris and her father try to make every ones last day on earth as pleasant as possible. She meets her brother in North Africa, he is getting a tattoo and she bawls him out for not helping.she then travels so fast she manages to tell her father "Good night. I love you" and goes off trying to stop what ever will end the world opposed to make every ones final day nice. After Barry tells Wally this and says 'I never understood that little fruit fly.' Wally responds with 'Don't call her "fruit fly." That's not her name. Her name... is Kid Flash.'

Good old Iris West!
name: Quick Fix

description: A woman named Rose works at Booster Gold's super memoribillia resteraunt Planet Krypton. A shrinking violet, Rose is lacks confidence in herself. But at night, at the empty restaurant, she encounters the ghosts of those lost in the Crisis- those that died, and those that never existed anymore. We learn more about Rose's less than happy past, while Booster calls in a ghost buster The ghost buster concludes that the ghosts are caused by time travelers weakening the walls of reality. Ultimately, Rose manages to overcome her dependance on the past, and some travelers from the future of Kingdom Come are caught by Batman.
name: Haunted

volume.name: The Kingdom: Son of the Bat

description:
Dsseldorf, West Germany, 1986. Everyone experiences feelings of uneasiness and self-doubt in their lives, and brilliant Dr. Kenzo Tenma is no exception. When he ignores his boss's orders and saves the life of a critically wounded young boy, Tenma must question the meaning of success and what it truly means to be a doctor. What is justice and what is evil? Who could have ever known that Tenma's selfless act would create a monster!

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 1 : Herr Dr. Tenma
  • Chapter 2 : Kill
  • Chapter 3 : Downfall
  • Chapter 4 : Brother and Sister
  • Chapter 5 : Murder
  • Chapter 6 : The BKA Man
  • Chapter 7 : Monster
  • Chapter 8 : Night of the Execution
name: Herr Dr. Tenma

description:
Dsseldorf, Germany, 1995. Against the backdrop of a recently unified Germany, middle-aged childless couples are being killed one after another. Dr. Tenma soon discovers that his ethical conduct as a doctor led to a disastrous consequenceJohan, the child whose life he saved less than a decade ago, is the culprit! Thus begins Tenma's desperate pursuit of Johan. His first goal is to find Johan's twin sister, who may hold some clues to the secret of the monster!

  • Chapter 9 : The Girl from Heidelberg
  • Chapter 10 : Prince on a White Horse
  • Chapter 11 : News Article:Missing Child
  • Chapter 12 : A birthday of Terror
  • Chapter 13 : House of Tragedy
  • Chapter 14 : It's Not Your Fault
  • Chapter 15 : Pursued
  • Chapter 16 : The Girl and the Seasoned Soldier

description:
Tenma races to Berlin to uncover the mystery of Johan's past, where he discovers a horrifying truth about experiments conducted in the former East Germany. Who is Johan really, and what is the ominous 511 Kinderheim? In the midst of this treacherous chase, Tenma falls into Johan's trap and becomes wanted for the serial killings he's trying to stop. Barely escaping the police, Tenma tries desperately to prevent the next murder and prove his own innocence.

  • Chapter 18 : Lawyer's Rules
  • Chapter 19 : 511 Kinderheim
  • Chapter 20 : Project
  • Chapter 21 : A Little Experiment

  • Chapter 23 : Petra and Heinz

description:
Intent on killing her twin brother, Nina infiltrates a neo-Nazi group based in Frankfurt that Johan has allied himself with. Unfortunately, her cover is blown and she's being held captive by the ultra-rightists. Meanwhile, Tenma's pursuit of Johan has also led him to Frankfurt where he makes two startling discoveries: Nina is close by, and the neo-Nazis are conspiring to set Johan up as a second Hitler.

  • Chapter 26 : Be My Baby

description:
"Look at me! Look at me! The monster inside me is getting bigger!" In an attempt to decipher Johan's enigmatic message, Tenma visits Dr. Gillen, an old college friend who is now a famous criminal psychologist. However, Dr. Gillen concludes that it's Tenma who has committed the murders, and he tries to set him up for his own experiments.

  • Chapter 34 : Jurgen's Basement
  • Chapter 35 : After the Carnival

  • Chapter 37 : Happy Holidays
  • Chapter 38 : Gun Barrel Vengeance
  • Chapter 39 : A Sunny Tomorrow
  • Chapter 40 : Runge's Hope
  • Chapter 41 : Runge's Trap

description:
Driven by love and hatred, Eva persists in pursuing her former fianc Tenma. One day in her down-and-out life, she meets a mysterious man... Who is he and what are his intentions? Meanwhile, meet Munich University student Karl Neumann. To earn money for his school expenses Karl visits a blind billionaire on a weekly basis and reads books to him. Strange events start to occur after Karl meets a young man who also reads to the billionaire. The young man's name is Johancould he be the Johan?

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 2: Rock Bottom
  • Chapter 3: Eva's Confession
  • Chapter 4: Of Men and Dining
  • Chapter 5: The Unseen Enemy
  • Chapter 6: Tuesday's Boy
  • Chapter 7: Thursday's Boy

description:
Richard Brown lost his job on the police force when he committed a fatal error on the job and, giving himself up to drink, he is abandoned by his family. Attempting to start life anew as a private detective, Richard is hired by influential financier Hans Schuwald to look into a personal matter. Deep in the investigation, Richard encounters Johan, who has worked his way into Schuwald's trust and is now his right-hand man. Could it be that Johan intends to take a leading role in Germany's economic market? Richard senses something sinister behind it all, as though he is battling some unknown monster... Will Johan's plans ever be brought to light?

Chapter Titles

  • Chapter 51 : Richard
  • Chapter 52 : Proof
  • Chapter 53 : Brought to Light
  • Chapter 54 : Just One Case
  • Chapter 55 : Johan
  • Chapter 56 : Execution
  • Chapter 57 : Decision
  • Chapter 58 : Reichwein's Days
  • Chapter 59 : In Broad Daylight
name: Richard

description:
Tenma keeps a tight watch on Johan's every move, and one day he is presented with a perfect opportunity: Johan will be attending a ceremony at the Munich University library. Armed with a high-performance rifle, Tenma decides to lie in wait for Johan, ready to pounce on his prey. Meanwhile, Johan has been laying low because he knows Tenma is out for his life. When he happens to open a Czech children's book in the library, he bursts into tears and loses his senses. What could possibly be the significance of this picture book, and why did it cause such a reaction in Johan?

  • Chapter 60 : Can You Prove It?
  • Chapter 61 : After the Party
  • Chapter 62 : Sanctuary
  • Chapter 63 : A Child's View
  • Chapter 64 : Mankind's Legacy
  • Chapter 65 : At the Edge of Darkness
  • Chapter 66 : Shine the Light
  • Chapter 67 : I Am Tenma
  • Chapter 68 : My Nameless Hero
name: My Nameless Hero

description:
Armed with a high-performance rifle, Tenma is ready to assassinate Johan at the university library. Will Tenma finally be released from his life as a fugitive? Meanwhile, the question remainswhy did the curious Czech children's book have such an upsetting affect on Johan? Could the book be a clue to solving the mystery of Johan's birth? Then an overwhelming sense of dj vu overtakes Nina as she reads the words of the book: "Once upon a time, in a land far away, there lived a nameless monster. He was dying to have a name. So the monster made up his mind to set out on a journey to look for one."

  • Chapter 1: A Greater Monster
  • Chapter 2: The Beast of Chaos
  • Chapter 3: A Nameless Monster
  • Chapter 4: Feast of Ants
  • Chapter 5: The Demon in My Eyes
  • Chapter 6: A Letter From Mother
  • Chapter 7: Traces of Heart
  • Chapter 8: The Hell in His Eyes
  • Chapter 9: The Frogs of Fairyland

description: Captain America: Proud member of the Avengers, but hes a man out of time, frozen for decades and unaccustomed to modern life. Can the Sentinel of Liberty learn to fight alongside heroes 60 years younger than himand why does Cap feel a strange connection to the man named Korvac? Ben McCool (Choker) brings you an epic tale ten centuries in the making!
name: Strange Days

description:
"Cedok Bridge, the three frogs...the mother of the twins is in Prague." A cryptic message from wealthy financier Schuwald sends Tenma to the city of a hundred spires. Along the way, he meets Grimmer, a freelance journalist tracking down the true story behind the 511 Kinderheim orphanage. Later, Grimmer gets himself mixed up in a bizarre serial murder case. Who could the real murderer be, and who is the beautiful woman Grimmer saw at the scene of the crime?

  • Chapter 79 : Picnic
  • Chapter 80 : The Ghost of 511
  • Chapter 81 : The New Experiment
  • Chapter 82 : The Key
  • Chapter 83 : The Adventures of Magnificent Steiner

description:
After Grimmer and Suk come across a cassette tape containing a recording of Johan talking about his birth, they get the feeling they are being hunted down. Could their pursuers be members of the former secret police, or Johan himself? Things get even more complicated when Suk meets a beautiful girl at a bar...and her name is Anna! Meanwhile, Tenma tracks down an apartment building in downtown Prague with the sign of the three frogs. He learns from the neighbors that ten years ago, a woman lived there with twins. Tenma also learns about an incident there involving a fire and the Czechoslovakian secret police. Could these twins have been Johan and Anna?!

description:
For Tenma and Grimmer, a mysterious blonde beauty is the prime suspect for the murder of the former director of 511 Kinderheim. They set out to find her but come up empty-handed. Meanwhile, Inspector Lunge is finally convinced of Johan's existence and involvement in the serial murders. He goes to Prague to find out more about Johan's identity and discovers that the storybook, The Nameless Monster, had a profound effect on Johan as a child, and that it was created by an agent of the Czechoslovakian secret police. This clue leads Lunge to the Red Rose Mansion where the author wrote his books. There, Lunge discovers an old door that has been plastered over. What horrors lie in wait behind this sealed door?

  • Monster Chronicle
  • Chapter 96 : A Long Vacation
  • Chapter 97 : Detective Boys
  • Chapter 98 : The Cruelest Thing
  • Chapter 99 : The Border City

description:
After his arrest in Prague, Tenma is deported to Dsseldorf. However, one of the lawyers appointed to his defenseRobertois actually an ardent follower of Johan! Roberto reveals his intent to kill Eva, so in order to save her, Tenma prepares to escape from prison by first admitting to the false charges against him. However, Eva still bears a deep hatred toward Tenma and refuses to testify on his behalf, even though she's capable of proving his innocence. Meanwhile, the sinister hand of Roberto inches closer and closer to Eva...

Chapter Titles

  • Monster Chronicle
  • Chapter 105 : Monster's Love Letter
  • Chapter 106 : The Prison Escapee
  • Chapter 107 : The Lawyer
  • Chapter 108 : The Witness
  • Chapter 109 : Determination
  • Chapter 110 : The Dirty Sandwiche

description:
Hoping to save Eva's life, Tenma succeeds in escaping from prison and heads to Red Rose Mansion. His only clue is a notebook left to him by the attorney Verdeman. Meanwhile, Nina, who has been struggling to regain her memories, also arrives at Red Rose Mansion. When she opens a sealed door inside that sinister building, a horrific scene from her past comes rushing back. Tenma, Nina, and Johan all converge on the mysterious Red Rose Mansion. What really happened there and who is Franz Bonaparta?

  • Monster Chronicle

  • Chapter 115 : The Never-ending Journey
  • Chapter 116 : The Puppet Master
  • Chapter 117 : The Children of the Recital
  • Chapter 118 : That Night
  • Chapter 119 : What Johan Saw

description:
Eva can identify Johan, and that's why she's been abducted and taken to Frankfurt by an extreme right-wing organization bent on making contact with Johan. Martin, the bodyguard who was been hired to protect Eva, is ordered to kill her because her "job" is now completed. Tenma is also in Frankfurt to confront Johan, but... Lastly, Nina, who remained in Prague to regain her childhood memories, finally has a breakthrough! What happened to Nina and Johan when they were children and what really transpired at Red Rose Mansion?!

  • Monster Chronicle
  • Chapter 123 : The Party Is Over
  • Chapter 124 : The Man Who Saw the Devil
  • Chapter 125 : The Devil's Friend
  • Chapter 126 : The Man Who Knew Too Much
  • Chapter 127 : A Sad Reunion
  • Chapter 128 : Nina's Memory
  • Chapter 129 : Memories of the Recital
  • Chapter 130 : The Door to Memories
  • Chapter 131 : A Pleasant Dinner Table

description:
After a long pursuit, Tenma finally gets a line on Johan's whereabouts while Nina confronts Peter Capek, the boss of the extreme right-wing organization and a survivor of Red Rose Mansion. Capek prepares to tell Nina the terrifying truth behind her and her brother's births, but who can truly know Johan, a man who gives nothing of himself to anyone and is totally uninterested in the desires of others? Where is he going and how did he become such a monster? The mystery continues to unfold, but will the truth ever be known?

  • Chapter 137 : Footsteps of Terror

description:
Nina has regained her memory and stands face-to-face with Johan! She finally opens up about the secrets behind Red Rose Mansion and the truth surrounding the monster's birth. Meanwhile, Lunge and Grimmer arrive at a small town in the German countryside. Who could they be looking for?

Once upon a time, there was a peaceful, quiet little town. Unbeknownst to its inhabitants, a monster, living in disguise, was dwelling there as well. The monster renounced its evil past and dedicated its life to helping the townspeople, but one day, several evil strangers arrive. The town is plunged into chaos when the populace begin slaughtering one another. It turns out that those evil strangers are actually trying to capture the monster, and its name is Franz Bonaparta!

  • Monster Chronicle
  • Chapter 142 : I'm Back
  • Chapter 143 : The Place to Be
  • Chapter 144 : Ruhenheim
  • Chapter 145 : A Quiet Gunshot
  • Chapter 146 : The Vampire's House
  • Chapter 147 : The Town of Suspicion and Fear
  • Chapter 148 : The Perfect Suicide
  • Chapter 149 : The Peaceful House
  • Chapter 150 : The Town Massacre
  • Chapter 151 : Memories Not to Be Forgotten
name: I'm Home

description:
Ruhenheim, a peaceful, quiet town, has been turned into a war zone. What is the "perfect suicide" that Johan is planning? Can Lunge and Grimmer stem the flow of violence? What will happen when Tenma and Nina finally confront Johan? At last, the full truth about the monster's birth is about to be revealed!

How does a living, breathing human being become a fabrication? Simple: they eliminate everyone that knows of them or their past. One man attempted to do just that. He attempted to commit the perfect suicide but failed to wipe the slate totally clean. Now that same man, the nameless monster, is no longer a fabrication.

Harry Hill... on Hold!

description: If you thought the revelation of the Ghost Panthers identity was a game-changerprepare yourself for the aftershock! Perfect Storms campaign to annex Genosha kicks into high gear, but can the X-Men take down the foe with the face of a friend? Its Wakanda vs. The World...and X-Legend Chris Claremonts twistiest tale of international intrigue yet!
name: I of the Storm

description: Two Autobots felled in the past two issues and the punishment is only beginning! A shocking revelation and an unexpected attack begins the REVENGE OF THE DECEPTICONS, the storyline that leaves a lot more Autobots on the operating table, and their entire future on Earth in questionand also features the return of superstar artist DON FIGUEROA!
name: Revenge of the Decepticons Part 1: The Demolished Man

description: WHAT?! A GIANT COBRA EATING TOKYO?! And someone is RIDING it? Its up to G.I. JOE to stop it and take down the mysterious and evil organization known as COBRA and their new secret weapon: SERPENTOR! And theyve only got 52 manga-filled pages to do it in!
name: #2 (of 2)

description: Amidst Sith--on--Sith violence, lone Jedi Kerra Holt persists with her near--broken mission! Trapped behind enemy lines and still eager to follow through with help for the oppressed miners on Chelloa, Kerra strikes out on her own to rid the galaxy of at least one Sith Lord. But she's still incredibly green and ruled too much by her strong feelings, and keeping her plan on track might prove to be too much for the young Jedi...
name: Aflame Part 3 of 5

description:
As the shape-shifting baby monster implodes before their very eyes, the Bureau discover the real beast is feeding on grief and flesh for sustenance.

Written by Mike Mignola and John Arcudi and drawn by Eisner Award-winning artist Guy Davis (The Marquis).

"Davis is an absolute master of creepiness; he creates atmosphere almost effortlessly." -Newsarama
name: 5 of 5

first_appearance_teams.name: Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense

team_credits.name: Bureau for Paranormal Research and Defense

volume.name: B.P.R.D.: Hell on Earth - New World

description: A mysterious killer stalks the streets of New York City and it's up to Charles Fort, Prophet of the Unexplained, to stop the strange murders. Only with the assistance of an otherworldly being will Fort be able to close in on his prey and reveal the truth behind the killer's identity. But first the duo will have to escape the suspicion of City Hall and the clutches of the NYPD! Untold stories from the files of the father of paranormal investigation! Don't miss a single thrilling issue!
name: The Hunted

description: Doctor Tom really didnt know what he was getting into when he helped the mysterious woman, known only as Cat. On the run from the police, federal agents, and the equally mysterious Thane, Tom finally steps through one of Cats doors. Only to find that it may not be that easy to find one home.

Having escaped the templars, Gleam, Agmo, and the dwarf Minderel exit the Deep Roads in a camp under siege by a group of bandits. As the village burns Gleam must use her magic to put out the fires, as her father, the templar named Duty, is close on her heels. Having escaped, her fate is sealedshe must be killed. But can her father kill her as he did her mother?

COBRA wastes no time in sending the Brainwave Scanner re-programmed DARK SNAKE EYES to hunt down the rogue G.I. JOE squad. The Joes might stand a chance if they decide to trust STORM SHADOW and believe that he is on their side now, but

volume.name: G.I. Joe: A Real American Hero

description: Michael Monk falls further down the rabbit hole, climbing the ladder of success out of Colossus and into the Movement. With his family, his life, and his very his sanity at stake, the Mad Monk will do anything to achieve his mission goals, even if he has to step over the dead bodies of G.I. JOE to do it

The heat is turned way up on the group as the government is closing in on Nick and Anna, and threatening to shut them down once and for all! Nick is captured, and now it is up to Anastasia and the girls to prove his innocence! Meanwhile, Verne and Secret Skull discover the true identity of the culprit who stole Edgar Allan Poes skull and just what his mad plan was! Mystery and the macabre collide in this thrilling conclusion!

IDWs return to Konamis horror masterpiece continues! Jebediah Hellrider Foster has made his way to Silent Hill with his wife Esther. But hes learning his dark past has come with him, too, and theres no escaping the hellish shadows hes cast for all his violent life. By Tom Waltz (writer of Silent Hill: Sinners Reward and the Silent Hill 8 videogame to be released in 2011), with artwork by Menton3 (Zombies Vs. Robots Aventure). Featuring a character from the new videogame!

As the situation on Ceti Alpha V rapidly deteriorates, Khan struggles to find a way to keep his people alive in the face of planetary waste and devastation. Meanwhile, forces conspire against Khan to remove him from power, mercilessly capitalizing on Khans sole weakness: his beloved wife Marla

volume.name: Star Trek: Khan Ruling in Hell

description: The continuing adventures of James Pattersons hip characters from the hit novel Witch & Wizard! Our sibling heroes, Whit and Wisty Allgood, move forward with their plan to depose the One Who Is The One, with the aide of a friend operating within the very ranks of the New Order. Its an all-out war and a race against time as the good guys use their magical powers to set the world free!

Cardiff's resident alien hunters are back on case in these all-new issues of Torchwood, based on the hit BBC-America series! Issue #4 brings the conclusion of 'Shrouded' from Gareth David-Lloyd (Ianto from Torchwood) and Pia Guerra (Y the Last Man). Issue #5 begins 'Somebody Else's Problem' from Chris Cooper and Stephen Downey as Gwen faces an alien drug lord alone! And the back-up story 'Broken' continues in each issue.

Cardiff's resident alien hunters are back on case in these all-new issues of Torchwood, based on the hit BBC-America series! Issue #4 brings the conclusion of 'Shrouded' from Gareth David-Lloyd (Ianto from Torchwood) and Pia Guerra (Y the Last Man). Issue #5 begins 'Somebody Else's Problem' from Chris Cooper and Stephen Downey as Gwen faces an alien drug lord alone! And the back-up story 'Broken' continues in each issue.
name: Somebody Else's Problem; Broken part 5 of 5; Photo Finish part 1

description:
Only 5 issues are left in this adrenaline-laced series! Julie and Annie combine forces to fight their way through state-of-the-art security systems and the world's most formidable army. With nothing more than a shared body covered in Alloy 618, the odds are against them, but the girls must win to prevent the Phi Collider from destroying the planet!

In Alaska the team are hunting for the collider. They find a truck stop where Ivy had a package sent to and Julie wits outside and a snow fox comes and rests at her feet. The owner mentions the collider thinking they work there. Its an open secret and helps point them in the right direction.

Ivy opens the parcel in secret and inside is one of those control pads that Hong tried to put on Julie's wrist. The letter with it says they used half the alloy and reversed the charge on one pad as she specified and the finger she sent was dated at 27,500 years old.

Julie seems to be getting more knowledgeable as she grows taller and her skin is perfect making locals think she is a model or actress. They even want her autograph instead of payment. She signs Annie Trotter.

The crew head off trying to work out how to locate and infiltrate the collider.

As they drive Ivy phones for help, on the other end two women are relaxing on a sun drenched beach.

Being forced to spend eternity as a vampire--trapped in the mind and body of a child, with slaughter the only recourse for survival--is torture enough. But when Abby finds herself faced with a ruthless real--estate tycoon willing to do anything to get at the property she and her caretaker call home, far more monstrous torments await. In a small community torn apart by vicious men who are consumed by greed, wrath, and envy, she will learn which deadly sin is truly deadliest.

Taking you even deeper into a tragic world of sophisticated horror with Let Me In: Crossroads, a chilling prelude to the highly anticipated film Let Me In.

Funny Misshapen Body is the story of Jeffrey Brown's evolution as a cartoonist, from his youthful obsession with superhero comics to his disillusionment with fine art at the School of the Art Institute of Chicago.

Drawn with Brown's scratchy, spare, trademark style, Funny Misshapen Body resonates with true-to-life observations on love, fear, and ambition. Through his bare bones graphic style, he reveals his most embarrassing personal moments in raw, intimate detail -- including how he survived high school, binge drinking, mild drug experimentation, doomed friendships, and being diagnosed with Crohn's disease.

Ultimately coming to terms with his art and identity, Brown describes the ups and downs of his adolescence with understated simplicity, dark humor, and charm.
name: Funny Misshapen Body: A Memoir

description: Autobiographical cartoonist Jeffrey Brown provides an epilogue to his Girlfriend Trilogy, detailing the day-by-day events of a three week run-in with five different girls. Watch and be mesmerized by an ex coming back into the picture, a growing but poorly chosen crush, musings on the way friends come and go in life and a realization that the end is never really the end.
name: Every Girl Is The End Of The World For Me

volume.name: Every Girl is the End of the World for Me

description:
From the imaginative mind of Joe Benitez with colors by the incomparable Peter Steigerwald, comes this all-new supernatural action-adventure series! The tabloids dubbed her 'Lady Mechanika', the sole survivor of a psychotic serial killer's three-year rampage through London. Found locked in an abandoned laboratory amidst countless corpses and body parts, with her own limbs amputated and replaced with mechanical components, her life began anew. With no memory of her captivity or her former life, Lady Mechanika eventually built a new life for herself as a private detective, using her unique abilities to solve cases the police couldn't or wouldn't handle. But, she has never stopped searching for answers... Now, brought into a case unlike any before, Lady Mechanika will have to rely on her advantage in all things occult and paranormal in order to solve the case and possibly unlock the secrets to her past!

description:
Overview:

The series of Warren Ellis flip-book Softcovers continues in this volume, reprinting the explosive espionage-thriller RED and the action-packed giant-robot adventure of TOKYO STORM WARNING! In RED, Ellis and artist Cully Hamner (BATMAN: TENSES) bring us a stark tale of revenge, as retired CIA killer Paul Moses finds himself forced back into the game to gain revenge on the agency that trained him! In TOKYO STORM WARNING, Ellis joins James Raiz (Transformers) for a tale of giant robots taking on atomic monsters in Japan's capital city in a desperate clash for survival and supremacy!
name: "Red";"Tokyo Storm Warning"

description:
Overview:

Collects Reload (2003) #1-3 and Mek (2003) #1-3. Written by Warren Ellis. Art by Paul Gulacy, Jimmy Palmiotti, Steve Rolston and Al Gordon. Covers by Gulacy and Rolston. Two fantastic miniseries from master storyteller Warren Ellis collected in one great flip-book trade paperback! RELOAD, with art by Paul Gulacy & Jimmy Palmiotti (CATWOMAN), is an espionage thriller that tells the story of Secret Service Agent Chris Royal and his mad scramble to find the woman who assassinated the U.S. President. MEK, featuring art by Steve Rolston (Pounded) & Al Gordon (TOM STRONG) is a tale of revenge set in a not-too-distant feature, where robotic enhancement has become the latest trend. This book will be printed in the flipbook format, with each story featuring a separate cover! For more information, see the feature article.
name: "Reload"; "Mek"

description: Shooting from the pages of ATLAS, comes an all-new exploration of fan-favorite GORILLA MAN! Yes, Ken Hale is blessed with might and cursed with inhumanity, but you don't know the entire tale, and how his history may destroy his present! See his storied past as an Agent of Atlas, a soldier of fortune, an ally of the Avengers, and a Howling Commando! Plus, learn the history of Marvel's Gorilla Men in 'Tales of the Gorilla Man' and then watch as Ken Hale takes the X-Men on a journey through the jungle in X-MEN: FIRST CLASS #8. Collecting GORILLA MAN #1-3 and material from AVENGERS VS. ATLAS #4.
name: TPB

description: He has a R on his shirt, but hes not Robin. Whos the mysterious kid in the Batcave with the orange hair? Is it Clayfaces kid? Maybe Jokers son? Hmmmm.

THE PRINCE OF POWER IS BACK WITH ONE, FINAL ADVENTURE AS ONLY BOB LAYTON CAN TELL IT!

Hercules has been the champion of the Andromeda galaxy for over 75 years! But when an attempt to save the capitol city of Port Anteris goes awry, the Lion of Olympus is left incapacitated and needing to be looked after by his Olympic offspring. However, with a sinister plot brewing against his son's government and the threat of Galactus looming, Hercules-even in his brain-addled state- is the galaxy's only hope! It's the long awaited follow-up to Bob Layton's classic Hercules run!

Collecting HERCULES: TWILIGHT OF A GOD #1-4.
name: Hercules: Twilight of a God

description:
The Lion of Olympus has fallen. And as the Heroic Age dawns, the Golden Mace of Hercules passes to a new Prince of Power...who just happens to be Herc's best friend, Korean-American kid genius Amadeus Cho. But when Amadeus finally reveals what he plans to do with his new power, the heavens themselves may shatter as Marvel's mightiest pantheons are shaken to the core! And wait a minute...what's THOR doing here?

Fan fave writers Greg Pak and Fred Van Lente and beloved 'Thorcules' artist Reilly Brown bring the thunder with the next essential chapter in the mind-blowing, heart-wrenching, and gut-busting epic that is the 'Incredible Hercules' experience! Plus, when the most beloved Olympian of all time falls, who will mourn him? Acclaimed artist Ariel Olivetti joins Pak and Van Lente for a mini-epic that marks the end of an era and the beginning of something utterly unexpected for Hercules, the Lion of Olympus.

Collecting HEROIC AGE: PRINCE OF POWER #1-4 and HERCULES: FALL OF AN AVENGER #1-2.
